title: HELP! Can't transfer .mdb file to other PC
author: KimiUser
text: Hello everyone! My father is a gastroenterologist and has been using an outdated yet amazingly effective program to store his patients records. However it is now time for him to upgrade to a newer laptop. He installed the program on the new laptop, however upon transferring the save file to the new laptop, it would only load records up to like 10 years ago. On his old laptop he can edit files as well as add new records without any problems, however, he can't seem to find a way to transfer the save file with all the data. There is no other save file on his computer and the file extension is .mdb. The company that made the program is no longer active! The program was developed for Windows 98. Any help would be greatly appreciated!

title: I got my first dataset from python neural networks today!
author: Ferocious_Armadillo
text:
I got my first dataset from ML code today!

I am going back school for my masters in bioengineering and have always been fascinated with coding and, more and more recently, become fascinated with machine learning and neural networks. I started working under a professor where I (hopefully) will get to contribute to research in his lab. A few days ago he pointed me in the direction of some source code for networks that will sort images of different pathologies. After only a couple of days I got my first dataset today! Just wanted to share what really feels like a win‚Ä¶ I‚Äôve never thought of myself as ‚Äúgood‚Äù at programming despite taking a couple of classes and teaching myself. [D]

Then I went to sites where I can talk with companies directly, I got an interview from 80% of the applications.

Now I went back to the recruiter sites, 0 reply out of 40 applications.

I used the same CV, and since once I‚Äôve made the mistake of giving my phone number (and have been constantly spammed for months), I‚Äôm not giving my number anymore, just email.
